And actually, Porto has some surprisingly good documentation on Word styles, if you

00:14:08.239 --> 00:14:10.280
need some documentation on it.

00:14:10.280 --> 00:14:14.440
And so then you can either adjust the styles yourself, or you can actually copy and paste

00:14:14.440 --> 00:14:16.880
styles between documents.

00:14:16.880 --> 00:14:21.520
So if you have a nice reference document, you can go ahead and use that.

00:14:21.520 --> 00:14:22.520
Great.

